By ET Now | 11 May, 2016, 12.17PM IST
Centrum Wealth Research maintains hold on SKS Microfinance post March quarter results with a 12-month target price of Rs 657.
SKS Microfinance reported yet another quarter of impressive financials in Q4FY16 with NII (net interest income) growing by 74.4% YoY, backed by 84% growth in non-AP gross loan portfolio (GLP).For FY17, SKS has set a target disbursements of Rs16,500 crore and gross loan book of Rs11,000 crore which translates into a growth of 37 per cent and 43 per cent, respectively.
"We forecast a loan book CAGR of 33 per cent over FY16-18E to Rs9,133 crore.
SKS continues to enjoy healthy financials (strong growth, RoA of +5%, and gross NPA below 0.5%), justifying its premium valuations," said the brokerage note.
